# Partial multiclock equivalence for VID (AGENT.md §6, README Tier 2). VID is two-clock (pclk
# raster + clk DMA) and its framebuffer-fetch CDC deliberately departs from VID60.v (our toggle
# pulse-synchroniser vs the RTL async-set req1), so a whole-VID equiv cannot close at the CDC.
# We prove AROUND it. Driven by Yosys_equiv.run_proof; placeholders (named WITHOUT braces here
# — substitution is blind): stubs = vid_stubs.v (DCM/BUFG port shapes); rtl = VID60.v; ours/gate
# = our emitted gate; top = VID.
read_verilog {stubs}
read_verilog {rtl}
read_verilog {ours}
# match our pixel width
chparam -set RGBW 6 {top}
hierarchy -check
proc
# drop VID60.v's Xilinx DCM/BUFG (a Phase-7 primitive) and expose pclk as a free clock like ours
delete {top}/c:dcm {top}/c:clkbuf
expose -input {top}/w:pclk
# cut the framebuffer word to a shared free input on BOTH sides, so the pixel datapath proves
# bit-exact GIVEN the same fetched word, without comparing the (departed) fetch timing/address.
# Gold: VID60.v's vidbuf register. Ours: the ping-pong read mux, NAMED vidbuf for this pairing
# (lib/vid.ml) — same role (the word pixbuf loads); the prefetch banks buf0/buf1 feed only it,
# so cutting it makes the whole prefetch front-end (banks, parity, look-ahead) irrelevant here.
expose -input {top}/w:vidbuf
expose -input {gate}/w:vidbuf
opt
equiv_make {top} {gate} equiv
hierarchy -top equiv
# exclude the TWO deliberate departures from VID60.v, both fed only by their now-excluded output:
#  - req:    our toggle pulse-synchroniser vs the RTL async-set req2 (the CDC; closed formally by
#            the vid_invariant property proof).
#  - vidadr: our 2-group prefetch look-ahead vs the RTL's current-group address. That the
#            look-ahead DELIVERS the correct word (Org + ~vcnt:col, the RTL's own address) into
#            pixbuf is closed by DECOMPOSITION, not here: the look-ahead address ≡ a geometry spec
#            (the vid_addr check, combinational Sec/z3 over all hcnt,vcnt) + vid_invariant (timing)
#            + a reviewed composition lemma. The monolithic all-phases proof does not converge
#            (col 0 is cross-line, the frame top cross-frame) — see test/formal/README "VID prefetch".
# What remains proven ≡ VID60.v here: the raster (hcnt/vcnt/hs/vs/blank → hsync/vsync) + pixel
# datapath (pixbuf → RGB), GIVEN the same fetched word.
equiv_remove -gate equiv/w:req %ci t:$equiv %i
equiv_remove -gate equiv/w:vidadr %ci t:$equiv %i
opt -full
equiv_simple
equiv_induct
equiv_status -assert
